# Primitive Quantum Channels

Placeholder for the theory of primitive quantum channels.

## Main results (planned)
* A quantum channel is primitive iff it is irreducible and aperiodic — Wolf Theorem 6.7
* Primitive channels have a unique full-rank fixed state
* Convergence: `Tⁿ(ρ) → σ` for the unique fixed state `σ`

## References
* Wolf, *Quantum Channels & Operations*, Theorem 6.7
